Sentencas: The anodic reaction of a dense Pd film in a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) was investigated by using BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-alpha (BCY) as an electrolyte.
Titulo: Anodic reaction of dense Pd film in SOFC using Y-doped BaCeO3-Effect of mixed ionic conduction of electrolyte

Sentencas: The anode performance of the film was better than the anode performances of porous Pd and Pt at 873 K.
Titulo: Anodic reaction of dense Pd film in SOFC using Y-doped BaCeO3-Effect of mixed ionic conduction of electrolyte

Sentencas: Although protons were predominant conduction in the porous Pt anode, oxide ion conduction and hole conduction slightly occurred in it at 873 K.
Titulo: Anodic reaction of dense Pd film in SOFC using Y-doped BaCeO3-Effect of mixed ionic conduction of electrolyte

Sentencas: In contrast, in the dense Pd film anode, small oxide ion conduction was compensated by hole conduction at 873 K.
Titulo: Anodic reaction of dense Pd film in SOFC using Y-doped BaCeO3-Effect of mixed ionic conduction of electrolyte

Sentencas: Hence, proton conduction occurred predominantly and hole conduction occurred to a small extent in it.
Titulo: Anodic reaction of dense Pd film in SOFC using Y-doped BaCeO3-Effect of mixed ionic conduction of electrolyte

Sentencas: However, at 1073 K, its performance decreased considerably because partial oxide ion conduction could not be inhibited by the dense Pd film.
Titulo: Anodic reaction of dense Pd film in SOFC using Y-doped BaCeO3-Effect of mixed ionic conduction of electrolyte

Sentencas: At the same temperature, conduction of oxide ions of BCY occurred predominantly in the porous Pt anode.
Titulo: Anodic reaction of dense Pd film in SOFC using Y-doped BaCeO3-Effect of mixed ionic conduction of electrolyte
